# Local Vite / workerd (detached)

Agents use the **detached** manager so Vite outlives shell reaping. URL:
`http://localhost:5173/` (prefer `localhost` over `127.0.0.1`). Foreground
`npm run dev` is for humans with an attached terminal.

| Command | Use |
|---|---|
| `npm run dev:status` | Health check first |
| `npm run dev:start` | Bring up if down |
| `npm run dev:stop` | Stop managed process |
| `npm run dev:restart` | Only when restart is justified |
| `npm run dev:logs` | Read `.dev-server.log` |

PID/log: `.dev-server.pid` / `.dev-server.log` (gitignored). Catalog:
`scripts/README.md` → `scripts/dev-server.sh`.

## When to restart

- Server is down / not responding (`dev:status` fails, connection refused)
- User explicitly asks to restart
- After changes that need a **full process** restart: env/secrets (`.dev.vars`),
  Wrangler bindings, Vite config, dependency install — **not** routine source
  edits (HMR covers those)

## When not to restart

- Routine code changes
- “Being helpful” or prophylactic restarts
- Prefer `npm run dev:status` (or a quick health check) first; only restart if
  down or the user asked

## How

- Prefer `npm run dev:start|stop|restart|status|logs` over raw `npm run dev` /
  `pkill` / stacking extra Vite instances
- `dev:start` / `dev:restart` may need unsandboxed/`all` permissions (sandbox
  can fail with `uv_interface_addresses`)
- Prior deaths were mostly reaped agent shells or `pkill`, not app/code errors
